      description: 'Crew is a small, multi-year advisory group of 10-15 students that meets daily or several times per week. The crew leader (a teacher) stays with the same students for multiple years, creating sustained relationships. Crew is where students set goals, track HOWLs, celebrate growth, and process challenges. The phrase "We are crew, not passengers" comes from Outward Bound co-founder Kurt Hahn.',
      whyItMatters: 'Belonging is the precondition for learning. When every student is known well by at least one adult, attendance rises, behavior referrals fall, and academic risk-taking increases. Crew is the structural answer to anonymity in middle and high school.',
